{"word":"H6617 - פָּתַל - pâthal - paw-thal' - Froward","slug":"H6617","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">פָּתַל</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>pâthal"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>paw-thal'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Froward"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05E4;&#x05BC;&#x05EA;&#x05DC; - pa&#x0302;thal</b> - <i>paw-thal'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>twine</i>, that is, (literally) to <i>struggle</i> or (figuratively) <i>be</i> (morally) <i>tortuous: - </i>(shew self) froward, shew self unsavoury, wrestle."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H5319\">H5319</a>, <a href=\"#/H5321\">H5321</a>, <a href=\"#/H6616\">H6616</a>, <a href=\"#/H6618\">H6618</a>, <a href=\"#/H6619\">H6619</a>"}]}